---
title: Slow-Cooker Chipotle Pork Sloppy Joes on Brioche Buns with Carrot Raisin Slaw
description: Don’t you wish you could just press play on a recipe and let dinner assemble itself? Guess what: it’s possible with a slow cooker. Break out the machine for these family-friendly sloppy joes, which feature a chipotle pork filling on a brioche bun and are accompanied by a crisp carrot raisin slaw. They’re so simple, all you have to do is put your ingredients inside the cooker base and let the magic happen. Just make sure to plan ahead—the cooking takes 6-8 hours depending on the heat setting.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/slow-cooker-chipotle-pork-sloppy-joes-8a73ecc7.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/slow-cooker-chipotle-pork-sloppy-joes-5a53ade02c3e081a7e34a322-c69e04ab.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/slow-cooker-chipotle-pork-sloppy-joes-5a53ade02c3e081a7e34a322
author: Sara Heilman
course: main course
time required: 8 hours
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 760 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 74 g
  sugar: 30 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1240 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), keeping greens and whites separate. Whisk together @water{1/2%cup}, @ketchup{4%tablespoon}, @adobo sauce{2%tablespoon}, @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp}, @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce}, @Dijon mustard{3%teaspoon}, @sugar{4%tsp}, @garlic powder{2%teaspoon}, and @chipotle powder{1/4%tsp} inside your #slow cooker{}.

> Add up to ¼ tsp more chipotle for extra heat.

Stir scallion whites into mixture in slow cooker. Season generously with @salt{}. Break up @ground pork{20%ounce} with your hands into crumbles and add to slow cooker, giving it a gentle stir to incorporate. Cover slow cooker with #lid{} and cook on high heat for ~{6%hours} or low heat for ~{8%hours}.

After starting slow cooker, toss together @shredded carrots{8%ounce}, @golden raisins{2%ounce}, @white wine vinegar{2%tbsp}, @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, @sugar{1 1/2%tsp}, and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} in a #medium bowl{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{}. Let marinate in refrigerator while filling cooks. Place scallion greens in a covered #container{} and reserve until meal is ready.

Once filling has finished cooking, season with @salt{} and give it a stir. Heat broiler or #toaster oven{} to high. Split @brioche buns{4} in half and place cut-side up on a #baking sheet{} (or toaster oven tray). Spoon filling onto cut side of bun bottoms, then sprinkle filling with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/2%cup}.

Place sheet under broiler (or in toaster oven) and allow cheese to melt and buns to toast, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Keep an eye on things, making sure that the buns don't burn.

Carefully remove sheet from broiler or toaster oven.

Thinly slice @dill pickle{1}(thinly sliced) crosswise, then divide between buns, layering onto filling and cheese. Cover with bun tops to create sandwiches. Stir reserved scallion greens into slaw. Season with more @salt{}, if needed. Divide sandwiches and slaw between plates and serve.